
    Brexit: Donald Tusk tells European Union to approve deal

        

    
        
                
                Image copyright
                 AFP
                
            
            
        European Council President Donald Tusk has recommended that the EU approve the Brexit deal at a summit on Sunday.It comes after Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez dropped his threat to boycott the summit after reaching an agreement over Gibraltar.He said he had received the written guarantees he needed over Spain's role in the future of the British territory. UK Prime Minister Theresa May flies into Brussels later to hold talks with top EU officials, ahead of the summit.
            

